Text: Re CES Updatefirst invoice for million went out a couple of weeks ago CES came back to us and said they were not going to pay They claimed that the total of all of the invoices to this date that they have already paid had covered that amount I have researched all of their invoices and it looks like there was a demand invoice in the system for the month of June for approximately million to much CES incorporated a credit for that invoice in with the charge for million netting out to approximately I am meeting with CES on Thursday to see if we are in agreement The other invoice for million was sent out last week CES is in agreement and the payment should be here shortly If you have any questions dont hesitate to call me Molly x Robert Superty PM To Molly CT cc Subject Re CES Update Molly please see Scotts note below and give us an update Thanks Bob Forwarded by Robert SupertyHOUECT on PM Scott Neal PM To Robert CT cc Subject Re CES Update What is the status of these invoicespayments Robert Superty PM To Sally CT Scott CT Brent A CT Bryce CT cc Molly CT Subject CES Update FYI ongoing CES reconciliation At this point we will be receiving app M invoice sent on with another M to be billed to them next week Still more to come for details read the attached from Molly Bob Forwarded by Robert SupertyHOUECT on PM From Molly Sumrow PM To Robert CT Victor CT Beverly CT cc Subject CES Update Attached is the current status of the CES reconciliation Please call me if you have any questions Thank You Molly

Welcome to CommodityLogicSusan Scott You have been created as a CommodityLogic End User Please find your new UserLogin ID below Please note that your UserLogin ID and Password are case sensitive and must be used in the format entered during registration CommodityLogic URL Your UserLogin ID CL Password password Upon logging into CommodityLogic you will be asked to load the java plugin This process will only take a minute or two If you feel it is taking an unusual amount of time to load please call us Also there is a registry file on the pipeline login page highlighted in blue Please double click on it and open it answer yes to both questions and you are all set The last thing you need to do is go into your control panel from your start menu and double click on your Java Plug In Make sure the box that reads Cache Jars in Memory is NOT checked This will allow you to receive all new releases of NomLogic If you have any further questions or suggestions please feel free to contact me If you require technical assistance please feel free to contact CommodityLogic by phone at or by email at Sincerely Molly Sumrow X
